cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the analysis of a propaganda campaign carried out by the Russia-based Internet Research Agency (IRA) on social media and search engines. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which deals with the study of social networks and their impact on society. The paper also involves the use of data mining and machine learning techniques to analyze the spread of propaganda, which falls under the category of cs.CY (Computational Geometry). The paper also deals with cybersecurity and the detection of malicious activities, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the study of political campaigns and their impact on elections, which falls under the category of cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). Finally, the paper involves the use of search engines to track propaganda campaigns, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
